  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf. \u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0d9c\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Pa. A petition from MP Gayashan",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Podujana United Peramuna's Monaragala District Member of Parliament Mr. Gayashan Navanandana has filed a fundamental rights petition before the Supreme Court requesting an order to prevent his removal from the post of Member of Parliament.",
        "Democratic Left Front leader Vasudeva Nanayakkara, Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna General Secretary Advocate Sagara Kariyawasam, Secretary General of Parliament, Election Commission and others have been named as respondents in this petition filed by Vidanapathirana Association Law Firm.",
        "The complainant stated in his complaint that he, who is a doctor by profession, was expelled from the party membership by the Central Committee stating that he acted contrary to the decisions of the Democratic Left Front.",
        "The petitioner has requested to issue a notice to the defendants in this regard as it is against the principle of natural justice as well as against the law and unfair action without holding any fair hearing in this regard."
      ],
